title: cts:bounding-boxes produces wildy innaccurate box
description:
Consider this timezone:

  http://tzmap.nwalsh.com/?tz=America/Belem

If you compute the cts:bounding-boxes that cover that region, you get several crazy boxes that stretch down towards the antarctic:

  http://tzmap.nwalsh.com/?tz=America/Belem&res=polyboxes

The query below shows one of them.

I think it happens in 5 and 6.

changeHistory.comment: Actually, I know it happens in 5 because tzmap.nwalsh.com is running on 5.0-3!
are you sure that none of these points cross the poles?  I think that is verboten, but not sure.
If you look at the first link, you'll see that the polygon is around a small region around a town in Brazil. No where near the poles.
Please investigate and clone if necessary.

Fixed 7.0-20130710

Note: there will be slight regressions in geosf-boundingboxes and srg-geosf
(box will have N bound of 41.667397 instead of 40). I believe this is OK.
